===Etymology===
Transliteration of Arabic [[سلفي]], meaning "predecessor" or "ancestor."<ref>[http://muttaqun.com/salafiyyah.html Dawat-us-Salafiyyah (Call of those who preceded us)]</ref>

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A [[Sunni]] Islamic movement that takes the pious ancestors, the salaf of the [[patristic]] period of early Islam, as exemplary models.<ref>Moosa, Ebrahim. ''Ghazali And The Poetics Of Imagination'' ISBN 0-8078-5612-6 p. 21</ref>

